entries.femaleVariant: Left a few peeps behind at the airstrip, rest went with Hellman.
You were right. Nomads' car did die.
These tracks lead up past the hill to an old filling station.
Drones, patrols... definitely set up shop here.
I see. They must have Hellman locked up somewhere.
We'll know soon enough.
All I see is cracked concrete and rust. If they thought they would call their friends, they were in for one helluva surprise.
I would have done the same. They're looking to call their people. The last they want is to ride through the desert without backup.
They tried to put her back on her feet. But the oil pump died, pistons couldn't take it.
That's one of our... one of their rides. Let's check it.
Headed west.
Mhm. But only two cars this time.
Dunno if we'll find anything else here.
Enough. There's nobody here.
Better check where Kang Tao took him. Fast.
Gave us a few minutes, maybe. But they still got a head start.
The rest must've taken Hellman with them.
If they manage to regroup and call for help, we're out of luck.
Better hurry, then.
Scorpion said I would hate Night City.
Wipe them out, V!
That's for my friends, you assholes!
Watch out! There's a sniper behind the van!
He knew you that well?
Probably better than I know myself.
That corpo, stole some sorta prototype. Think it was Militech. You don't remember? Anyway, chased the guy through three states, only to fish his body up outta the lake.
He said when I'd had enough of the city, we would get ourselves an RV.
Careful, V.
I hope Mitch contacted the Aldecaldos. All that damned interference...
I wager that's where they're holding Hellman.
They're comin' for 'im, don't worry.
But V, see that? The pumps look pretty good. Not what you would find if the place were closed.
The bastards might have managed to call for transport.
Scorpion said I would hate Night City.
Heard it's beautiful there. And that Ryan Diemer's car is rusting at the bottom.
What? Who?
Killed himself?
Doubt it. Think they hit him with a virus. Anyway, lost control. Probably suffocated before he could drown.
That is fucked up.
But you stopped thinking about all that sad shit for a moment, right?
Hah.
He knew you that well?
Probably better than I know myself.
He said when I'd had enough of the city, we would stock up on canned kibble...
Sounds like a real adventure.
Yeah... but he's gone. Shit, V, why is everything shit, shit, shit...
Hey, I know... But look, you're alive. Still got a few things to take care of, too.
Mhm. You know it.
Do you know what?
What?
This is my life right here. I step out of one pile of shit, only to trip into another, bigger one.
Panam...
And pull in everyone else after me.
I'm done. You hear me, V? I fuck up again, you'd better give me a good kick in the ass.
But you didn't fuck anyth--
Promise me.
All right, I promise.
Gas station â€“ see it?
Bet that's where Kang Tao's all settled in nice 'n' cozy.
Gotta be holdin' Hellman inside.
Better not waste time. Little shit must be bored to death.
Our guys were here.
Let's follow, find them.
Fill a couple of thermoses with coffee and whiskey, and hit the road. He said we would get away from it all.
Then we'd stock up and hit the road. Crater Lake. That was his big dream.
